messages.content: Illuvies and Malachite appear with a flash, and he lets Malachite fall to the ground, dusting himself off. “My performance *definitely* could’ve gone more swiftly..” he murmurs before turning to Malachite and smiling. “*Hello* my shining emerald!”
He scrambles to his feet and backs away, looking at him warily.

“Aww, what’s with the silence? Nothing to say to little old me~?” he asks, pouting, before holding his arms out. “Come on, Malachite dear, don’t you recognize me?”
His silhouette is fully shown now.

"Don't call me *dear,"*
He spits, trying to get his bearings.
"Who are you, and where are we?"

He once again pouts, placing a finger on his cheek. “Well, isn’t that disappointing. You truly don’t recognize me..?” 
He sighs softly, closing his eyes in defeat. “Oh well.. no matter, you shall learn of me soon..”
He snaps, and suddenly three silhouettes appear. One with wings, the other on the ground kneeling, and the last...
It stood next to the winged silhouette, before swiftly making it’s way to the real thing.

The two silhouettes behind him trembled in fear.

Illuvies held out his hands once again, which the silhouette mimicked. “*Tada~!* Remember me now, sweet pea?”

He steps back, breath catching as his eyes flit between the figures. *...God.*
"Mhm,"
He gives a shallow nod.
"I- yeah, who the hell are you?"

“My name—“ he began, holding out his arms, sparkles flying everywhere... dramatically. “—Is Illuvies the Shining! And you~” he announced, pointing at Malachite, “*most likely* will not be okay after this performance. NO MATTER! You are a *strong* companion to dear Polaris, no matter what you know, you will fight through it. Now~”
He warped behind Malachite, gripping his face again and keeping his eyes open. “*Observe,*” he whispered sweetly into the others ear. In front of them, the silhouettes began to move. This time, you could *hear them.*

Helio whimpered weakly, unable to fight with seven *entire* Plasma there. *Oh god.. Polaris... I’m so sorry..* he thought to himself. 
“It was unavoidable, my darling” Illuvies (from the past) began, holding Helio’s face and squishing his cheeks as if he were a child. “Polaris is *such* an *intelligent* child, this was positively *bound* to happen sooner or later. I suppose it just goes to show..” Illuvies stood up, walking over to Polaris.. he was screaming. “..What happens when you *defy* a higher being. Would you like to observe, my dear Helio? To view just what *your reality bending ability* is doing to him?”
Helio whimpered again, backing up a few steps and shaking his head. “No.. No— No, please, st—stop this..!”
“I’ll take your cries as an absolute *yes!*” he responds with a sickly evil smile. A screen pops up to their side, and Helio covers his mouth, shaking his head and eyes wide with Horror. *Thousands* upon *millions* upon *billions* of deaths played on the screen, each one more blood-filled than the last.
“Now *THAT* is what I like to call *character development!*” he cackled out happily.

"Get- *Jesus*, get the hell off me-"
“I will have to decline,” Illuvies declines respectfully, picking up Malachite and bringing him closer to the screaming silhouette of Polaris. “Wouldn’t you like to continue the show~?”

Malachite writhes in his grasp, pissed off to *no* end. He *hates* this polite facade.
*"Don't talk to me like that,"*
He hisses.

“Oh, but why not, my dear? It is purely how I am!”
He grins wickedly, shoving Malachite’s face in front of Polaris’ agonized one. “*And that is purely how* **he** *is..~*”

He pulls away, swearing and trying to claw at Illuvies' immaculate scarf.
"Fucking *bastard-* let *go* of me-"

“Oh, but Malachite, dear,” he pouts, his scarf going and wrapping itself around Hierophant, balling it up and holding it tight. “You wouldn’t want to leave *dear poor Polaris* by himself, now would you~?” he asks, a screen forming in front of them. Polaris sits on his bed in #sleeping-areas , hurling out whats left of an empty stomach off the side of the bed. His skin is pale, sweaty and disgusting, and he attempts to grab for water before gagging again. “He must need your help, no?”

"Fuck you,"
He spits.

“..”
His brow furrows, and suddenly he slams Malachite’s face into the ground, standing up tall above him. “My dear, dear, *beautiful* shining emerald.. you are being much more *uncooperative* than I had hoped you to be. Must I truly stoop to Morise’ level? I would hate to do such a thing.”

"Whore."
It hurts a bit to get words out, but at least this fucker is actually attacking him now.

“...”
He stays silent, but holds his hand out, cupping it as if he’s holding a glass of water. He waits for Malachite’s reaction.
He stands up and spits shimmery green blood on Illuvies' shiny white clothes. *Fuck you.*

“....”
Just as it hits, the Polaris on the screen disappears.. and suddenly he’s hanging from his neck in Illuvies’ grip, eyes wide with pure fear and gasping for air.

He grimaces at the sight, but refuses to aknowledge it further. He meets Illuvies' eye again for a moment and makes his way over to where Hierophant is tangled in scarf. *He isn't giving this sadistic fuck a reaction.*

“Ah ah ah~” he sings, wagging a finger at Malachite and tightening his grip on Polaris’ neck, dark purple lines starting to form on him. “Not so fast, my dear~. I know you do *truly* care for him, I’ve been watching your romance,” he smiles, placing his hand on his cheek. “Oh, so sweet, oh but don’t fret, my dear, I made sure to avoid watching your frisky times,” he made sure to add in, reassuring Malachite of the wrong thing at the moment.
*”M-M’lach-chite—“* Polaris chokes out, trying to hold a hand out to the other. *“R-Run...”*

He wrinkles his nose in digust.
"What the fuck do you want me to do?"
He turns to look at him.
"Why am I here? Do you want a fight, you sick fuck?"

“...”
He lets go of Polaris, though something invisible continues to hold him in the air, and he chokes. Illuvies struts towards Malachite, bending down to his level. “How intriguing.. out of all I have played with in my billions of years of life, *you* are the only one who will not fall ill to temptation.. *astonishing.*”

He steps away.
"Maybe because you decided to show me that you can make illusions, *dipshit.* That-"
He gestures to the struggling Polaris, holding down revulsion.
"...that's fake. Do better."

With a snap of his fingers, a hole opened up in the strange world, showing the *real* Polaris in #sleeping-areas , still hurling even with nothing left to hurl. Illuvies appears, standing a bit away from Polaris, Somnus and Seiko. "Welcome, my dear, to my humble abode!"

She looks around, swiveling her head nearly completely backwards as she takes it in.
"Lovely!"
She hums quietly,
"Uh, do you have a bed, or something similar? They need to rest, I think."

With the swish of his hand, a large king sized bed appears. "Reality as we know it can be whatever I want it to be, here! Just say the word, and all your wildest fantasies will be true as the air we breath!"
The fluffy jacket dumps Polaris onto the bed lazily.

"Thank you, friend,"
She sets Seiko on the bed carefully, trying to settle her into a comfortable position.
"This place is fancier than mine- I always seem to make things, uh... *strange.* Things don't turn out right there.'

"Well, that makes sense, I suppose. I am much more prim and proper than you, to no offense, I can hope. Anyways.."
He swings his hand again, and a screen appears, Superbia and Lunara's interactions playing. "It seems that Superbia is feeling better, although she's taking a much deserved break from the Plasma zone. I know not of Morise' whereabouts at the current moment, but I will know them soon."

"I am... glad, that Superbia is doing well. I don't *hate* her."
She looks over at him, tapping her cheek.
"You saw what happened, yeah?"
"Of course. You completely smashed her lower half into a million bits, just like Morise with Polaris' upper. Quite the show."
"Mhm. It wasn't as... delicate as I would've liked, I guess? She deserved a more dignified knee smashing."

"Hm.. No, the back alley of a waffle house was most certainly not the most *ideal* place to smash a knee. Though, I suppose time *was* of the essence.. I have not had a good knee smashing in a while, you know. I'd do it to Riri here, but I think that with his top half already compromised.. It would be a tad bit overkill."
"It would be tasteless. At this point, I think *most* things would be too much for him- that's why I initially started, uh, fucking around."
"I see.. Well, at least we can simply fix him up," he exclaims enthusiastically, bringing his hands together and closing the screen.
"Yeees- if you create a medical pack here, will it function?"

"Of course! Well, no, not exactly. You see, I simply have a storage of them here— I'm not immortal, you know— Not by *far.*"
A sort of sliding door opens up, revealing an entire room of.. god knows what. A med kit comes flying out, bumping into Somnus' chest, and the door closes swiftly after.

"Oof- thank you."
She catches the case, inspecting it.
"So *this* is where you keep your shit."

"Well, yes, I suppose."
He jumps into the air, letting himself drift along casually. "There is a serum in there— It allows for quick healing in mere *seconds.* Quite the technology."

"Ooooo,"
She opens the case and draws out a bottle, staring at it wide-eyed. *Maybe she shouldn't have skipped out on learning general Plasma knowledge."
*"Very* cool- how does it work?"
"You simply inject it into the wound, and voila!" He springs his hands in the air for more exaggeration.
"Cool! How does it *work?"*
"It simply mends the cells back to their original state."
"...What is it made out of?"
"I do not make it, so I am unaware."

She nods, still blinking at the serum.
"I'm sorry for the questions- I will not stop asking them though. Where do Plasma acquire the packs?"
"I do not know."

"Hmmmm,"
She uses a syringe to draw the liquid out, tapping it to make the bubbles rise to the top.
"Interesting- do they have factories on the Plasma home world?"
He drapes himself over his jacket, sighing dramatically. "Oh, *possibly*. It's been *eons* since I've visited that old fart of a galaxy— Quite boring, they all ate."

"Glad I'm not missing much."
She plunges it into Polaris' arm, using her ability to prevent him waking up from the pain.
After only a few moments, his arm is considerably less swollen and more back to the color it was before, with less blood underneath the skin. "See? Works like a charm."

"Ohh, *interesting."*
She slides it out, looking around for something to drop it into.
"Can you make a, uh, a biohazard bin, please?"
His fingers snap, and a decently sized big appears, clanging onto the ground next to Somnus.

She tosses it in.
"Should I use another, or will this do the trick?"
"Mm.. Perhaps use another— Not too much, though. Don't want to overload his system and cause his cells to continuously grow into a horrid cancer."

"Ooooh, a horrid cancer? *Interesting-* does it do that to Plasma also?"
She draws out another syringe, filling it only about a quarter of the way with the fluid.
"...Asking for normal reasons."
"Well, I suppose it may.. Although, I can only assume it's not that titanic of a problem— We can merely shapeshift it away, or cut off the limb infected."

"Very cool."
She injects him again, only using about half of the liquid.
"Have you, uh, tried that before? The cancer thing."
He coos, placing his cheek in his hand. "Oh, most certainly. One of the other council members left after I experimented on him. Oh, the memories~!"

She chuckles.
"I wish I could have seen it- I've been trying to be less evil recently, but I *do* really like the idea of fucked up supercancer."

"*Absolutely!* It's a fantastically intriguing concept, is it not?"
He chuckles back at her, looking up into the white nothingness as he relaxes, hands behind his head. "Of course, I also attempted to give *myself* the strange cancerous defects. I lost a leg that day— Nothing I couldn't just shapeshift back, but *my,* was *that* an experience!"

"Ohhh?"
She looks at him, eyes shining excitedly.
"Did you take pictures?"
"Of course! I won't show them right about now, but just know it was *excruciatingly* painful. It felt like my skin as I knew it was tearing apart and bursting like a balloon at the seams!"
"Oooooh, maybe I will try it sometime. Would you recommend?"

"Unless you'd rather not feel the unbearably agonizing pain of each and every cell in your body ripping to shreds while simultaneously shoving themselves back together all in the wrong place, then absolutely!"
"Mmmmaybe, if I get bored enough- it *might* be better than sleeping for a few thousand years."
"Aren't you in love, at the current moment? Would that not worry the poor lass to death?"
((i only ever hear 'lass' be said in a scot accent, so now i.... is illuves scottish???

"Yeeees, perhaps."
She looks down at Seiko, tilting her head.
"...Saying that I'm in love is *weird.* Am I in love?"

"... I don't think Morise could kill me, not easily at least. As long as I get the jump on them, I could, uh- probably have a chance."
She sighs and looks back at him.
"If... if something *does* happen, though, will you keep taking care of things for me? I'd like to be a little bit useful, at least."

"..."
He giggles, covering his mouth with his hand politely. "You are *very* similar to Polaris, are you aware, Somnus?"
((ASSIGNED POLARIS KIN

She sticks her tongue out.
"I have *some* sense of self preservation, at least. I don't *intend* on dying, I just... I want to know I've left something behind, if I do."

He pauses for a moment.
"Somnus I know I said I would not aid you in saving the Kujo's— *Though I suppose I am right now*— But that sentence does not apply to you. You are my friend, and I will protect you, if I must."

She looks at him, at a loss for words for a moment- they're close, but she didn't know he actually *cared* that much.
"I... thank you, friend,"
She smiles a little,
"...I'm glad you care for me enough to help."
His scarf floats him over, and he looks at her upside down, smiling wide. "Of course, my dear! You're the closest I have ever been to a person! I would hate to lose you so soon.."

She mirrors the expression, reaching up to ruffle his hair.
"...That means a lot from you."

"Ah!"
He gives her a wide eyed look, pleased. "You're being physically affectionate! This is quite the difference from before!"

She withdraws her hand a little and shrugs.
"I guess... I guess I figured I might-might as well, uh, do that. Since I'm being nice now, or, uh- something."

"My dear, you have not a single bad bone in your *body.* At least, in comparison to mine self~" he says, bumping into her hand for a moment. "You're learning to leave the shell you've formed around yourself. I'm proud of you, my friend."

She gives him another slightly awkward pat before drawing her hand back and resting it on her face.
"...Thank you. I just hope I can still be effective like this- I'm not built for anything this, uh... *soft."*
"Quite the ironic statement coming from the certain plasma who wears a jacket that is practically as fluffy as their own hair."
*"I* think it's *imposing."*
"Neither me, nor Seiko believe that to be so."
(( @dirt.eater guess who passed out fully clothed in their beeed
(it be like that!)
"...I will not change it. It is comfortable, and I am still scary."
"I am not declaring you *change* it. I think it's quite adorable, and completely fits your fuzzy-mothy-nature. I'm merely explaining that fluffiness typically equates cuteness."
"Fluffy things can be scary- like honey badgers, and those fucked up caterpillars that can hurt you."
"Both are dangerous, yes, but they are also seem as adorable."

"Mm, maybe so,"
She flops down beside the bed and stares up into the emptiness above her.
"Either way, I think the fluff got me a date- or at least *helped* me get one."
"So," a lounging chair springs up from under Somnus, bringing her to the same height as the bed beside her, "It's more for mating than intimidation."

"I-"
She flushes pink, sitting up to look at him.
"That isn't-"

He casually inspects his nails, cheek resting on the back of his other hand. 
"Am I wrong?"
*"...Yes?* I wasn't trying to *seduce* anyone."
"But you got yourself a mate."
"...I got a *date."*
"Yes. A possible mate."

"Mhm,"
She rests her hand on her face.
"Uh, maybe."
"She seems to like you, as well. I cannot experience romantic feelings, but I'm very happy for you!"
"Thank you. It's... interesting. I haven't, uh, felt... anything like this before, really."
"Well, friend," he floats over to Somnus, patting her shoulder. "If you are ever in need of assistance, I will *always* be here for you."

She looks up at him, smiling.
"I appreciate it, friend."
"Well!" he suddenly exclaims, fixing the collar of his hoodie. "You best be going now, I suppose! Lest Morise have the heads of the revolution leaders!"

"Ah- yeees, I have to go be distracting, huh?"
She slides off of the couch and straightens, brushing herself off.
"I'm going to go do some fuck-upping. Can you, uh, make me a door out of here?"
He nods, "Why of course!" and a door forms, leading back to the #sleeping-areas . "Now, if it comes to it, you need to know I *absolutely* will choose your life over theirs."

"...I wouldn't expect anything else, friend,"
She adjusts her cape, stepping backwards toward the door.
"Thank you again. Toodles!"

"Tatah~!"
And the exit shuts.

Polaris wakes up quietly, groaning softly as he sits up, moving his hand to his face. Wait— How did he..?
He blinks in confusion, holding his arms out in front of him. They're.. healed. They're healed? Did Somnus get some sort of kit and heal them quickly or something?
His head swivels from side to side, confused. Where.. *are* they? It look like his mindscape, except even the *sky* is white. There's.. *nothing.*

"Somnus..?" he says quietly, voice hoarse with unuse. In an attempt to push himself up, he just stutters again, catching himself haphazardly on his elbow, which almost gives out itself.. *God* he is sore. Is his crack still..?
Yep. His crack is still leaving his arm practically suspended on a string. *Fuck.*
He manages to just barely push himself up, swaying for a moment before managing to get his balance, holding himself up tiredly.
Again, where the hell are they..? Is this some sort of.. weird fucked up isolation chamber Morise made or something? A place to screw with their heads? He wouldn't be surprised.
"*Oh Polaris dear~!" Illuvies shouts to a clearly freaked out Polaris. He blinks in surprise, backing up and hitting hit back against the headboard. "Illu— *What the fuck—*"

"Polaris?"
Malachite steps forward, hesitating a few feet away from the bed. Is this some sort of fuckery? It doesn't *feel* like it, but he should still be careful.
"Fuck, what happened?"

Illuvies simply smiles, stepping to the side. Seiko wakes up from the shouting, groaning lightly before pushing herself up, rubbing her eyes. "Mm.. What's going on..? Is everything alright?"
"Uh. Wh— Wait, wait I'm confused—"
"You're in his creepy void dimension- did he just bring you here in your sleep? Are you hurt?"
"He *what!?* Seiko shouted, suddenly feeling a lot more awake as she shoots up, looking around in panicked confusion. "M-Seiko, c-calm down—"

He steps forward again, tentatively extending a hand.
"You- you said your arms were broken, are you alright? Or better, at least? Jesus-"

"I— S-Somnus used a the-thing, probably.. I think? I-I'm a bit numb.. still kinda hurts.."
Seiko was still calming down next to them, trying to ground herself.

He looks over the two of them, biting the inside of his mouth.
"... Can you walk?"
"Yeah, yeah.. J-Just a little shaken, I can walk."

He glances back at Illuvies and the doorway, then turns back to Polaris. They should get out quickly, while they have the chance.
"Mhm. Uh, Miss- Seiko? Are you badly injured?"
She shakes her head no. "I'm fine, dear.. give attention to my son, he's.. Not as well off as me."

He nods.
"Here-"
He extends a hand to him,
"Let's leave, yeah? I'll help you up- let's go home."

He takes a deep, shaky breath, before taking Malachite's hand and giving it a nervous squeeze. "Mhm. That sounds nice."
Seiko stands up, quickly walking to Malachite. "Morise didn't hurt you all while we were gone, did they..?"
"They haven't done anything. Ah- you disabled the wrist bracelets, right? You're not being tracked this time?"

"..Oh."
He looks at his wrist, which the bracelet wasnt.. actually taken off of yet. "..Forgot about that."

"..."
He looks back at Illuvies.
"...Do you know how the fuck this comes off?"
"Not a clue, he sighs," humming. "And even if it comes off, an alarm will sound. Wouldn't want that now would you?"

He turns around fully, eyes widening slightly.
"...You just *brought* them here? With the *tracking bracelets still on?"*
"Well, yes. They're still technically within the Plasma zone, so the alarm has not been set off— They have not been shocked."

He blinks at him.
"... So... what the **fuck** do you want me to do? I- chop off their hands?"
"Well, that does seem like a plausible options," he hums, laying his hand out limply. "What!? No! That's a horrible idea!" Seiko shouts in protest.

Of *course* Illuvies would pull some horse piss like this. 
"Do you have some kind of fucking- shrink ray, or something? Can you break the bracelets?"

"If I break them, it'll set off an alarm," he muses, feign checking his nails. "If they leave their wrists, it'll set off an alarm. Chopping them from their wrists seems to be the most plausible option, darling."

*Asshole.* He turns back to the people in the room he actually cares about.
"...Fuck, do you have any other ideas?"

"P-Perhaps someone can hack into it..?" Seiko offers up, not much worrying for her own hand, but her sons.. She can take the pain, she's a strong lady, but her son just recently had *both his arms broken.* She's not sure he (or her, emotionally) could take much more of it.
"Maybe Nexum?"

"Who is Nexum?"
Polaris purses his lips in thought. "Aren't they the uh— the plasma? O-Or is that Radium— I-I'm a little out of it so.."

"Uh, Radium is the Plasma. *Shit..."*
He runs his hand through his hair, tugging at it. How does he know Illuvies isn't going to vanish while he looks for more options?
Illuvies appears behind the bedframe, his hands holding the top and his chin resting on the knuckles, relaxed. "I'm right here, not going anywhere, little birdie."

"Don't *call* me that-"
He cuts himself off, taking a moment to compose himself.
"I need to contact someone. Tesseracts work in here?"
"I-I have mine," Polaris says, pulling his tesseract out of his pocket and shakily holding it out for Malachite. He tries to calm down his violent trembling.
"No, thank you Polaris, I have mine, I'm asking if it can connect."

"O-Oh.."
He puts his tesseract back, a little embarrassed that he misunderstood. 
"Yes, you can work them in here," Illuvies hums, tilting his head to the side playfully.
He wrinkles his nose a little at Illuvies as he takes his tesseract out, idly ruffling Polaris' hair with his other hand.

He pushes into it shakily, hugging himself to try to stop his trembling— He *hates* it.
Seiko puts a hand on his back, rubbing circles into it soothingly.
He gives him a concerned glance and shuffles closer, leaning against the bed and pulling Polaris nearer to himself.
"S-Sorry, tryna.. Not be shaky. This is a lot," he mumbles, letting himself limply lean back against Malachite.

"Don't worry about it,"
He murmurs, gently smoothing hair away from his face.
"I'm taking care of everything."
He nods, letting out a shaky sigh. Seiko gives him a worried look, before turning to Malachite. "Do you know someone who can help..?"
"I think so, I'm trying to contact them. We... don't really talk much."
She nods, giving him a hopeful look. "I'll trust you."

"...Mhm."
He taps away at his tesseract for a moment, snaps a picture of Polaris' bracelet, then slips it back into his pocket.
"...She's coming. Might be a minute."

He nods again, sighing.
